00:06:53.460 --> 00:06:55.990
&gt;&gt; Janine Joseph: Leaving the
nonprofit immigration lawyer's

00:06:55.990 --> 00:06:59.630
office, 2001.

00:06:59.630 --> 00:07:04.500
When the car drifted from the Santa
Ana winds, I switched off the radio

00:07:04.500 --> 00:07:06.830
and pointed at the
street poles swaying

00:07:06.830 --> 00:07:10.230 position:56%
over the two-way stretch like palms.

00:07:10.230 --> 00:07:16.100
All night, the wind brushed dry the
hills with fire and I kept driving.

00:07:16.100 --> 00:07:20.180
His hands steady out the
window taking snapshots

00:07:20.180 --> 00:07:22.630
of the red, whipping rings.

00:07:22.630 --> 00:07:27.420
I power rolled the windows down
to let the smoked grass scent seep

00:07:27.420 --> 00:07:30.550
into the upholstery,
circulate coyote

00:07:30.550 --> 00:07:33.570
and birdsong through the air vents.

00:07:33.570 --> 00:07:37.300
"Can you smell the burning
mustard plants, the foxtail

00:07:37.300 --> 00:07:39.720
and fox glove weeds on my skin?"

00:07:39.720 --> 00:07:45.400
I asked. Hands open, the
wheel orbiting under my palms.

00:07:45.400 --> 00:07:47.110
Watch when I let go.

00:07:47.110 --> 00:07:51.490
I demonstrated, knuckles
loosening around the leather,

00:07:51.490 --> 00:07:56.050
the car coasting left with
pollen and butterfly debris.

00:07:56.050 --> 00:07:59.650
"We'd be pitched into the
brush glare," I warned.

00:07:59.650 --> 00:08:04.310
If I let go completely, we'd
grate the chain-linked fence

00:08:04.310 --> 00:08:07.430
and itch the ashen shrubs.

00:08:07.430 --> 00:08:11.880
I shuddered slow at tumbleweeds
storming the undercarriages,

00:08:11.880 --> 00:08:13.390
storming the road.

00:08:13.390 --> 00:08:17.310
B said, "Right, like you'd let go."

00:08:17.310 --> 00:08:23.250
Thank you, everyone for coming out
tonight to see Aimee and I read.

00:08:23.250 --> 00:08:25.980
Aimee is one of my literary heroes

00:08:25.980 --> 00:08:29.050
so this is a really
surreal experience.

00:08:29.050 --> 00:08:35.290
Thank you to Rob and Anya, and Rita
and Kundiman, and Jen and Lawrence

00:08:35.290 --> 00:08:40.670
for making this entire reading
and this collaboration possible.

00:08:40.670 --> 00:08:44.660
As Jen mentioned, I'm going to
be reading largely from my book

00:08:44.660 --> 00:08:51.120
which just came out this past May
and the book follows an immigrant

00:08:51.120 --> 00:08:54.810
from the Philippines who
is living in the U.S.

00:08:54.810 --> 00:08:57.560
without proper legal documentation.

00:08:57.560 --> 00:09:00.730
And the book is very much informed

00:09:00.730 --> 00:09:03.680
by my own experience
having lived undocumented

00:09:03.680 --> 00:09:05.960
in the U.S. for 15 years.

00:09:05.960 --> 00:09:11.020
I immigrated my family when
I was eight years old in 1991

00:09:11.020 --> 00:09:15.280
and did not get my green
card until my first year

00:09:15.280 --> 00:09:17.960
of graduate school at NYU.

00:09:17.960 --> 00:09:22.470
This next poem has so many parts.

00:09:22.470 --> 00:09:25.450
There's an epigraph which no
longer appears in the book.

00:09:25.450 --> 00:09:29.780
There are parts -- there are
sections and then there's language

00:09:29.780 --> 00:09:36.150
that is lifted from the U.S. CIS
N-400 form for naturalization

00:09:36.150 --> 00:09:41.300
as well as language that's taken
from a number of newspaper articles

00:09:41.300 --> 00:09:45.700
about undocumented immigrants,
undocumented immigration.

00:09:45.700 --> 00:09:48.310
It's called <i>Between
Chou and the Butterfly </i>.

00:09:48.310 --> 00:09:51.080
And again, I'll begin
with the epigraph.

00:09:51.080 --> 00:09:54.710
And for each section,
I'll just pause.

00:09:54.710 --> 00:09:58.780
He does not know whether he is
Chou who dreams he's a butterfly

00:09:58.780 --> 00:10:01.730
or a butterfly who
dreams he is Chou.

00:10:01.730 --> 00:10:05.980
Between Chou and the butterfly,
there was necessarily a dividing.

00:10:05.980 --> 00:10:07.800
Just this is what is meant

00:10:07.800 --> 00:10:10.100
by the transformation
of things -- Zhuangzi.

00:10:10.100 --> 00:10:13.810
Between Chou and the butterfly.

00:10:13.810 --> 00:10:21.500
On my way to America, I am
in an airplane, on a boat.

00:10:21.500 --> 00:10:26.600
When my life is a story, I am a
good swimmer, an American dream,

00:10:26.600 --> 00:10:32.210
a guest worker, freeloader, fence
hopper, uninsured brother carried

00:10:32.210 --> 00:10:35.820
from hospital to hospital,
a crushing case load,

00:10:35.820 --> 00:10:41.770
a wrenching anecdote, a
deserving young people and anchor.

00:10:43.470 --> 00:10:48.370
Before anyone finds me, I am
heartwood exposed by lightning,

00:10:48.370 --> 00:10:50.270
by the young Republicans,

00:10:50.270 --> 00:10:55.930
by newscasters playing find illegal
immigrant, find the unwed single,

00:10:55.930 --> 00:11:00.670
the crier, the spouse battered
by U.S. citizen spouse.

00:11:00.670 --> 00:11:04.510
Find the widower, the one
you will petition to marry,

00:11:04.510 --> 00:11:07.710
the headless bodies
in the Arizona desert.

00:11:07.710 --> 00:11:15.010
I hear they raid when you're naked
in bed, packed like a sardine,

00:11:15.010 --> 00:11:16.560
pillows tucked around you.

00:11:16.560 --> 00:11:21.490
I hear like dogs, like alien
relatives while you cry

00:11:21.490 --> 00:11:23.630
and hug, they swarm.

00:11:23.630 --> 00:11:25.910
They ax your back door.

00:11:25.910 --> 00:11:31.670
The trunks of trees, they ax
the wild terrain, the scrub,

00:11:31.670 --> 00:11:36.990
the rapid succession of sounds I
make when I walk alone and sweaty

00:11:36.990 --> 00:11:39.170
and hardly myself in the dark

00:11:39.170 --> 00:11:43.630
where a man migrating suffering
great pain is found hanging

00:11:43.630 --> 00:11:47.130
from a tree later charred.

00:11:47.130 --> 00:11:52.230
According to eyewitnesses, I am
the same crazy, lost on my way

00:11:52.230 --> 00:11:57.140
to dead man's tree, to the hallowed
tree of virgin in the valley

00:11:57.140 --> 00:12:01.690
of the lost ones, in the
wilderness stripped of my underwear

00:12:01.690 --> 00:12:06.470 position:56%
for the money stitched into the
seams, for mental status evaluation.

00:12:06.470 --> 00:12:11.720
A physical examination to
include complete disrobing.

00:12:12.920 --> 00:12:17.330
Worse than genital herpes, the
situation with these illegals

00:12:17.330 --> 00:12:20.620
into the microphone,
says the interviewee.

00:12:20.620 --> 00:12:26.430
"I, the undersigned, am not
a communist and not likely

00:12:26.430 --> 00:12:28.590
to become a public charge.

00:12:28.590 --> 00:12:33.710
I understand I do not traffic other
humans, recruit child soldiers.

00:12:33.710 --> 00:12:38.430
I do not seek to practice
polygamy, engage in espionage

00:12:38.430 --> 00:12:43.220
in ordered genocide in items
A through L. I do not have

00:12:43.220 --> 00:12:46.660
to reimburse the school
I do solemnly swear

00:12:46.660 --> 00:12:48.870
if I am not who I say I am.

00:12:48.870 --> 00:12:52.770
I may subject me to
permanent exclusion."

00:12:58.450 --> 00:13:02.300
Landscape with American dream --

00:13:02.300 --> 00:13:06.280
putting down the beets you got to
thinking my life had dead-ended

00:13:06.280 --> 00:13:11.230
and we're serious and I agreed
but first, "I need capers

00:13:11.230 --> 00:13:15.380 position:56%
and whatever is past the pimientos,"
I said and scanned the list.

00:13:15.380 --> 00:13:20.060
I needed the lemon glaze, the
stuff I craved on the ethnic lane

00:13:20.060 --> 00:13:24.680
and still I had to sing of how
I walked a thousand hot miles

00:13:24.680 --> 00:13:28.480
because my mom was Catholic
and pressed the white blouse,

00:13:28.480 --> 00:13:31.610
the blue jumper and
we were good people

00:13:31.610 --> 00:13:36.120
and good people lent their good
cars to those in more need.

00:13:36.120 --> 00:13:40.570
It was like the distance from
here to the Philippines, I nodded.

00:13:40.570 --> 00:13:42.830
I MapQuested it once.

00:13:42.830 --> 00:13:46.800
And they -- my brothers, were
all eyes on their Gameboys,

00:13:46.800 --> 00:13:50.820
dodging potholes, snake holes
and anthills from Saint Francis

00:13:50.820 --> 00:13:53.370
to who knows where we lived.

00:13:53.370 --> 00:13:58.780 position:56%
We walked so much my dad every night
kneaded the stiff backs of our shoes

00:13:58.780 --> 00:14:03.420
so they wouldn't scallop our heels
when we walked lesson after lesson

00:14:03.420 --> 00:14:05.500
without turning an ankle.

00:14:05.500 --> 00:14:07.400
What wrecks we were.

00:14:07.400 --> 00:14:11.800
What expert wrecks burning
down those sun sponged streets.

00:14:11.800 --> 00:14:15.970
Now look high muscle my stack
of avocadoes and hearts.

00:14:15.970 --> 00:14:21.040
See how I coast and carved
and fault my rootless cart.

00:14:21.040 --> 00:14:25.690
See how I course my
arm to say go and go.

00:14:25.690 --> 00:14:26.990
Do you wait for me?

00:14:26.990 --> 00:14:31.490
Do you circle the lots quiet
loop while I lift into a run

00:14:31.490 --> 00:14:35.210
like a dog dead and
slipped from her lease?

00:14:35.210 --> 00:14:36.540
Do you brake?

00:14:36.540 --> 00:14:37.840
Do you idle?

00:14:37.840 --> 00:14:40.050
Do you worry your arm from an aisle

00:14:40.050 --> 00:14:44.470
like a table sauce
saying come, come?

00:14:44.470 --> 00:14:47.280
I've a line to beat
and know double coupons

00:14:47.280 --> 00:14:48.970
so do you strike up your shoes?

00:14:48.970 --> 00:14:55.860 position:56%
Do you bare hand your grief and pump
it slack, lap after lap after me?

00:14:55.860 --> 00:14:59.920
Come, bread roadster,
come American galloper,

00:14:59.920 --> 00:15:02.970
come bark with this
breath out with me.

00:15:09.100 --> 00:15:11.420
I have one final poem.

00:15:11.420 --> 00:15:18.290
I had a first career when
I was three years old.

00:15:18.290 --> 00:15:22.710
I was the face of a Kraft
Cheddar Cheese in the Philippines.

00:15:22.710 --> 00:15:28.000
And this title takes the -- takes
its name from part of a jingle

00:15:28.000 --> 00:15:34.190
from a Kraft Cheddar
Cheese commercial from 1986.

00:15:34.190 --> 00:15:37.220
More milk, more milk
makes it better.

00:15:37.220 --> 00:15:44.060 position:56%
In 1986, when I was three-and-a-half
years old, I won an award

00:15:44.060 --> 00:15:49.360
for sitting cute and biting into
a slice of Kraft Cheddar Cheese.

00:15:49.360 --> 00:15:51.860
Then how my star blew up.

00:15:51.860 --> 00:15:55.850
I was on the cover of
calendars in the Sunday section,

00:15:55.850 --> 00:16:00.500
stomping the runway, turning
down small parts in movies.

00:16:00.500 --> 00:16:05.480
At seven, I promised my mom I
would never be chubby again.

00:16:05.480 --> 00:16:09.200
No way. I swirled a dress
in the dressing room

00:16:09.200 --> 00:16:12.450
and was the daughter
my brothers hated.

00:16:12.450 --> 00:16:15.530
